<collectingCountry id="F36C7669FF99E473A915539040A0FDF6" box="[359,419,511,535]" name="United States of America" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">USA</collectingCountry>
: MA.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC436F9FF99E473A8B5504D4501FD67" blockId="57.[151,1437,258,2014]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B90FEAEBFF99E473A8B5504D40A3FDDA" bold="true" box="[199,416,546,571]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Adult description.</emphasis>
Wing length approximately 2.0mm (
<specimenCount id="9D7DFD70FF99E473AB30504C425BFDDA" box="[834,856,547,571]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
) (poor condition, coated with residue), 
<quantity id="4C839B1CFF99E473AD65504C4465FDDA" box="[1303,1382,547,571]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2mm</quantity>
(
<specimenCount id="9D7DFD70FF99E473AD0B504C448FFDDA" box="[1401,1420,547,571]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
). Length of ultimate section of vein CuA1 divided by penultimate section: 2.8. Eye height divided by gena height: 8.4. First flagellomere small, rounded. Arista short pubescent. Notum shining.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3616572FF99E473A8B550FE4006FA7C" pageId="57" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC436F9FF99E473A8B550FE42F6FD13" blockId="57.[151,1437,258,2014]" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis id="B90FEAEBFF99E473A8B550FE4044FD4B" box="[199,327,657,682]" italics="true" pageId="57" pageNumber="58">Chaetotaxy</emphasis>
: Two ors, two ori in female; male with additional third anterior ori nearly as long as following seta. Ocellar and postvertical setae subequal to ors. Four dorsocentral setae, decreasing in length anteriorly, most markedly so on anterior two. Approximately five rows of acrostichal setulae.
</paragraph>
